org.pragmaticminds.crunch.api.values

Class TypedValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pragmaticminds.crunch.api.values.TypedValues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, CRecord, MRecord

    public class TypedValues
extends Object
implements MRecord, Serializable
    Class for Transporting "TypedValues" internally in CRUNCH. Is the pendant to UntypedValues for the Untyped case. It is one implementation of MRecord but as it holds all values typed in the Value classes (and inherited) classes it is very expensive to create and usually only a small subset of the Values is really requested.
    Author:
    julian Created by julian on 23.10.17

      • merge

        public TypedValues merge(TypedValues typedValues)
        Merges another set of typed values into this typed values and returns the merged set. This set is not updated!

        It is important that the Values Object that is given to be merged into has higher (or equal) timestamp and that both have the same source.

        Parameters:
        typedValues - Values to merge in
        Returns:
        Merged Values
